        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Code Interpreter Tool"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The code interpreter tool gives Claude a sandboxed Python runtime. Claude writes code, the sandbox executes it, and the output \u2014 text, images, data files \u2014 is injected back into the conversation. This enables data analysis, chart generation, file conversion, and mathematical computation without you writing a single line of execution logic."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Code interpreter execution flow diagram",
          "title": "Code Interpreter Flow"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Enable with tool type "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "code"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "'code_execution_20250522'"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". The type string has changed between API releases \u2014 always verify the current value in the Anthropic documentation before shipping."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Enabling the Code Interpreter"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Add the tool to your "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "tools"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " list. No other configuration is needed \u2014 the sandbox lifecycle is managed by Anthropic."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\nresponse = client.messages.create(\n    model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n    max_tokens=4096,\n    tools=[\n        {\n            \"type\": \"code_execution_20250522\",\n            \"name\": \"code_execution\"\n        }\n    ],\n    messages=[\n        {\n            \"role\": \"user\",\n            \"content\": \"Calculate the first 15 Fibonacci numbers and the ratio between consecutive pairs.\"\n        }\n    ]\n)\n\nfor block in response.content:\n    if block.type == \"text\":\n        print(block.text)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Reading Code Execution Results"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The response content may contain "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "tool_use"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " blocks (the code Claude wrote), "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "tool_result"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " blocks (the execution output), and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "text"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " blocks (Claude's interpretation). Iterate all blocks to collect the full picture."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\nresponse = client.messages.create(\n    model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n    max_tokens=4096,\n    tools=[{\"type\": \"code_execution_20250522\", \"name\": \"code_execution\"}],\n    messages=[{\n        \"role\": \"user\",\n        \"content\": \"Compute the standard deviation of [4, 8, 15, 16, 23, 42] and explain the result.\"\n    }]\n)\n\nfor block in response.content:\n    match block.type:\n        case \"text\":\n            print(\"[Text]\", block.text)\n        case \"tool_use\":\n            print(f\"[Code ({block.name})]\")\n            if isinstance(block.input, dict):\n                print(block.input.get(\"code\", \"\"))\n        case \"tool_result\":\n            print(\"[Output]\")\n            if isinstance(block.content, list):\n                for c in block.content:\n                    if hasattr(c, \"text\"):\n                        print(c.text)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Data Analysis with Uploaded Files"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pass file content using the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "document"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " content block type. Claude reads the file in the sandbox and can analyse, transform, or summarise it."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\ncsv_content = (\n    \"date,product,revenue\\n\"\n    \"2024-01-01,Widget A,1200\\n\"\n    \"2024-01-02,Widget B,850\\n\"\n    \"2024-01-03,Widget A,1400\\n\"\n    \"2024-01-04,Widget C,920\\n\"\n    \"2024-01-05,Widget B,1100\"\n)\n\nresponse = client.messages.create(\n    model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n    max_tokens=4096,\n    tools=[{\"type\": \"code_execution_20250522\", \"name\": \"code_execution\"}],\n    messages=[{\n        \"role\": \"user\",\n        \"content\": [\n            {\n                \"type\": \"text\",\n                \"text\": \"Analyse this sales CSV. Find total revenue per product and the top performer.\"\n            },\n            {\n                \"type\": \"document\",\n                \"source\": {\n                    \"type\": \"text\",\n                    \"media_type\": \"text/plain\",\n                    \"data\": csv_content\n                },\n                \"title\": \"sales.csv\"\n            }\n        ]\n    }]\n)\n\nfor block in response.content:\n    if block.type == \"text\":\n        print(block.text)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Chart Generation and Image Output"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When Claude generates a matplotlib chart, the sandbox captures the PNG and returns it as a base64-encoded image content block. Decode and save it to display or forward downstream."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic, base64, pathlib\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\nresponse = client.messages.create(\n    model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n    max_tokens=4096,\n    tools=[{\"type\": \"code_execution_20250522\", \"name\": \"code_execution\"}],\n    messages=[{\n        \"role\": \"user\",\n        \"content\": (\n            \"Create a bar chart of monthly rainfall in mm: \"\n            \"Jan=85, Feb=72, Mar=60, Apr=45, May=30, Jun=18. \"\n            \"Use a blue colour scheme and label each bar.\"\n        )\n    }]\n)\n\nfor block in response.content:\n    if block.type == \"text\":\n        print(block.text)\n    elif block.type == \"tool_result\" and isinstance(block.content, list):\n        for item in block.content:\n            if getattr(item, \"type\", \"\") == \"image\":\n                img_bytes = base64.b64decode(item.source.data)\n                out_path = pathlib.Path(\"rainfall_chart.png\")\n                out_path.write_bytes(img_bytes)\n                print(f\"Chart saved to {out_path} ({len(img_bytes):,} bytes)\")"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Mathematical and Statistical Computation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The sandbox includes numpy and scipy. Complex numerical tasks \u2014 matrix operations, statistical tests, optimisation \u2014 are accurate because they run in Python rather than relying on Claude's native arithmetic."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\nresponse = client.messages.create(\n    model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n    max_tokens=2048,\n    tools=[{\"type\": \"code_execution_20250522\", \"name\": \"code_execution\"}],\n    messages=[{\n        \"role\": \"user\",\n        \"content\": (\n            \"Perform a two-sample t-test: \"\n            \"Group A = [23, 25, 28, 22, 27, 24, 26], \"\n            \"Group B = [30, 33, 29, 35, 31, 28, 32]. \"\n            \"Report the t-statistic, p-value, and whether the difference is \"\n            \"statistically significant at alpha=0.05.\"\n        )\n    }]\n)\n\nfor block in response.content:\n    if block.type == \"text\":\n        print(block.text)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Multi-Step Analysis in One Request"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Claude can execute several code blocks in sequence within a single response, using the output of each step to inform the next \u2014 outlier detection, then re-computation, then visualisation \u2014 all without additional round-trips."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\nresponse = client.messages.create(\n    model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n    max_tokens=4096,\n    tools=[{\"type\": \"code_execution_20250522\", \"name\": \"code_execution\"}],\n    messages=[{\n        \"role\": \"user\",\n        \"content\": (\n            \"Temperatures: [22.1, 23.4, 21.8, 24.1, 19.9, 25.3, 22.7, 23.1]. \"\n            \"Step 1: Compute mean, median, and std. \"\n            \"Step 2: Identify outliers using the 1.5*IQR rule. \"\n            \"Step 3: Re-compute stats excluding any outliers found. \"\n            \"Explain each step.\"\n        )\n    }]\n)\n\ncode_blocks_run = 0\nfor block in response.content:\n    if block.type == \"tool_use\":\n        code_blocks_run += 1\n    elif block.type == \"text\":\n        print(block.text)\n\nprint(f\"Code blocks executed: {code_blocks_run}\")"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
