        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Streaming Code Execution Output"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Use "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "client.messages.stream()"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to stream text output while the code runs. This lets you display intermediate results in real-time rather than waiting for the full response."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\nwith client.messages.stream(\n    model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n    max_tokens=4096,\n    tools=[{\"type\": \"code_execution_20250522\", \"name\": \"code_execution\"}],\n    messages=[{\n        \"role\": \"user\",\n        \"content\": (\n            \"Generate a 10x10 multiplication table and print it formatted neatly. \"\n            \"Then compute the sum of all values in the table.\"\n        )\n    }]\n) as stream:\n    for text in stream.text_stream:\n        print(text, end=\"\", flush=True)\n    print()\n\n    final = stream.get_final_message()\n    code_blocks = [\n        b for b in final.content\n        if b.type == \"tool_use\"\n    ]\n    print(f\"\\nCode blocks executed: {len(code_blocks)}\")"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Handling Execution Errors"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When the generated code raises an exception, the sandbox captures the traceback and returns it as a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "tool_result"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " with an error flag. Claude reads the error and typically self-corrects by rewriting the code."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\nresponse = client.messages.create(\n    model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n    max_tokens=4096,\n    tools=[{\"type\": \"code_execution_20250522\", \"name\": \"code_execution\"}],\n    messages=[{\n        \"role\": \"user\",\n        \"content\": \"Divide the numbers [10, 20, 0, 40] one by one and print each result.\"\n        # This will cause a ZeroDivisionError \u2014 Claude should catch and handle it\n    }]\n)\n\nfor block in response.content:\n    if block.type == \"text\":\n        print(\"[Claude]\", block.text)\n    elif block.type == \"tool_result\":\n        if getattr(block, \"is_error\", False):\n            print(\"[Exec Error \u2014 Claude will retry]\")\n        else:\n            if isinstance(block.content, list):\n                for item in block.content:\n                    if hasattr(item, \"text\"):\n                        print(\"[Output]\", item.text)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "File Conversion and Text Extraction"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Beyond numeric analysis, the code interpreter handles text processing tasks: parsing JSON, converting formats, extracting structured data from unstructured text, or building data pipelines \u2014 all in the sandbox."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\nraw_log = (\n    \"2024-03-01 10:00:01 ERROR timeout on request /api/users\\n\"\n    \"2024-03-01 10:00:05 INFO  request completed /api/products (200ms)\\n\"\n    \"2024-03-01 10:00:09 ERROR connection refused to db-primary\\n\"\n    \"2024-03-01 10:00:15 WARN  high memory usage: 87%\\n\"\n    \"2024-03-01 10:00:22 ERROR timeout on request /api/orders\\n\"\n)\n\nresponse = client.messages.create(\n    model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n    max_tokens=2048,\n    tools=[{\"type\": \"code_execution_20250522\", \"name\": \"code_execution\"}],\n    messages=[{\n        \"role\": \"user\",\n        \"content\": [\n            {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Parse this log file. Count errors by type, and list the unique error messages.\"},\n            {\n                \"type\": \"document\",\n                \"source\": {\"type\": \"text\", \"media_type\": \"text/plain\", \"data\": raw_log},\n                \"title\": \"app.log\"\n            }\n        ]\n    }]\n)\n\nfor block in response.content:\n    if block.type == \"text\":\n        print(block.text)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Token Cost Considerations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Code execution adds tokens for both the generated code (output tokens) and the execution result (input tokens on the follow-up turn). Multi-step analysis with many code blocks can accumulate significant token usage. Profile with "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
